The paper focuses on the use of diversity mechanisms in evolutionary algorithms for dynamic optimization problems, which is a common topic in the field of neural networks (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with optimization algorithms (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY) in the context of dynamic constrained optimization problems. Finally, the paper involves differential evolution (DE), which is a popular optimization algorithm in the field of distributed computing (cs.DC).
